+++ b/notes/2026-06-19.md
@@ -52,7 +52,31 @@ experiment_planner: ✅ (handoff SHA 639a44)
 patch_planner: 🔴 (blocked — next stage)
 ```
 
+## Stage 3.6 patch_planner + 3.7 patch_applicator — Added
+- Created `pipeline/patch_planning_stage.py` — orchestrates PatchPlannerAgent → validation → PatchMaterializer → conflict analysis → ApprovalRequest
+- Created `pipeline/patch_application_stage.py` — loads approval → ControlledPatchApplicator → finalize → PatchRunnerHandoff
+- Wired orchestrator `_stage_patch_planner` and `_stage_patch_applicator` to real runners
+- Added `patch-plan` and `patch-apply` CLI subcommands
+
+## E2E orchestrator run (run_l3_bottle_001) — all 8 stages wired
+```
+intake: ✅
+repository_intelligence: ✅
+paper_intelligence: ✅
+research_context: ✅
+transfer_design: ✅
+experiment_planner: ✅
+patch_planner: 🔴 (blocked — empty variant hook_bindings produces no changes; needs real variant data)
+patch_applicator: 🔴 (blocked_upstream: patch_planner)
+```
+
+## Known limitations
+- `PatchMaterializer._generate_proposed_content()` returns unchanged content (stub — no LLM code synthesis)
+- Current variant's `hook_bindings` is empty, so 3.6 plan has no changes (data issue from demo)
+- 3.7 requires `approvals/patch_approval.json` with `confirmed_by_user: true`
+- 3.8–3.9 stages remain structurally blocked
+
 ## Leftovers / Next
 - Baseline contract auto-produce from repo artifacts needs enrichment
 - Paper intelligence short budget produces empty idea_sources (manual fallback used)
-- 3.6–3.9 stages remain structurally blocked
+- 3.8–3.9 stages remain structurally blocked
